///////****************************************************////
When you annotate your entity with @odata.draft.enabled in your service.cds file like this:
entity Finance @odata.draft.enabled {
  key No: Integer;
  ...
}

CAP (Cloud Application Programming Model) automatically adds two hidden keys to manage draft versions of the entity:
-IsActiveEntity (Boolean)
-HasDraftEntity (Boolean, for views)
-SiblingEntity (Association)

And when you try to access the entity by key like:
GET /odata/v4/financeservice/Finance(No=1)

It's incomplete, because you also need to specify IsActiveEntity, like:
GET /odata/v4/financeservice/Finance(No=1,IsActiveEntity=true)

